AB  - This paper presents a robust fast-terminal back-stepping control approach applied to a three-omni-wheel robot. For highly maneuverable and flexible robotic systems as three-omni-wheel robots, achieving effective control and precision tracking is a significant challenge. Through analyzing the kinematic and dynamic features of the system, mathematical models are thoughtfully proposed. Based on the Lyapunov stability and finite-time stability criterion and back-stepping scheme, we developed a control algorithm that allows the robot to track to the desired velocity trajectory, thereby ensuring the robot follows the expected shape on the global coordinate despite the disturbance impacts. The numerical simulations compared with classical sliding mode control are then implemented to validate the effectiveness of the whole work.
ER  - 

